"privacy_policy2" : " Fere fit Privacy Policy 

 Prompt Terms 

 Feredit platform refers to the Feredit mobile application software (APP) operated by Shenzhen Zhongwei Intelligent Information Technology Co., Ltd. 

 Fere fit (We) attaches great importance to users' privacy and personal information protection. When you use our goods and/or services, we will collect and use your relevant information. We hope to explain to you how we collect, use, save, share and transfer this information when you use our goods and/or services, and how we provide you with access, update, delete and protect this information through the Fere fit Privacy Policy (this Privacy Policy). This policy is applicable to the products or services of the Fere fit website (including PC, IOS and Android). 

 Before using the products or services on the Feredit website, you must carefully read this policy, and use the relevant products or services after confirming that you fully understand and agree. Once you begin to use the products and/or services on the Fere fit website, you have fully understood and agreed to this policy. 

 If you have any questions about this privacy policy or related matters, you can visit the online customer service system of Fere fit at any time and send an email to 936160908@qq.com Or call any of our customer service phones and other ways to contact us. 

 This privacy policy section will help you understand the following: 
 n 1. How we collect and use your personal informatio
 
 n 2. How we use cookies and similar technologies 
 n 3. How do we share, transfer and publicly disclose your personal informatio
 
 n 4. How do we protect your personal informatio
 
 n 5. How do you manage your personal informatio
 
 n 6. How do we handle minors' personal informatio
 
 n 7. How does this privacy policy update 
 n 8. How to contact us 
 n 1、 How we collect and use your informatio
 
 n We will collect and use your personal information for the following purposes described in this policy: 
 n User Registratio
 
 n First, you need to register a Feredit account to become a Feredit user. When you register, you need to at least provide us with your Fere fit account name and your mobile phone number. We will verify your identity by sending SMS verification code or email. If you only need to use basic services such as browsing and searching, you do not need to register as our user and provide the above information. 

 We will not ask you to provide additional personal information, nor will we affect the basic functions of your use of the products or services on the Feredit website. 

 Security 
 n In order to improve the security of your use of our products or services, and better prevent security risks such as phishing, fraud, network vulnerabilities, computer viruses, network attacks, and network intrusion, we may use or integrate your user information, order information, equipment information, network log information, and browsing information to comprehensively judge and investigate the risks in your account and transactions, and take necessary countermeasures according to law. 

 Other uses 
 n When you use our goods and/or services, you authorize us to receive, summarize and analyze your personal information or transaction information provided to us from our affiliates and partners according to the actual business and cooperatio
 needs. 

 We will use your information for other purposes not specified in this policy in accordance with the Cyber Security Law and other relevant laws and regulations, following the principles of legality, legitimacy and necessity. 
 n Exceptio
 
 n According to relevant laws and regulations, it is not necessary to obtain your authorization to collect your personal information in the following circumstances: 
 n 1. Related to national security and national defense security; 

 2. Related to public safety, public health and major public interests; 

 3. Those related to criminal investigation, prosecution, trial and execution of judgments; 

 4. It is difficult to obtain your own consent in order to protect the life, property and other major legitimate rights and interests of the personal information subject or other individuals; 

 5. The personal information collected is disclosed to the public by yourself; 

 6. Collect personal information from legally disclosed information, such as legal news reports, government information disclosure and other channels; 

 7. Necessary for signing the contract according to your requirements; 

 8. It is necessary to maintain the safe and stable operation of the goods or services provided, such as finding and handling the faults of the goods or services; 

 9. Necessary for legal news reporting; 

 10. Academic research institutions are necessary to carry out statistics or academic research based on the public interest, and conduct de identification of the personal information contained in the results when providing academic research or described results; 

 11. Other circumstances stipulated by laws and regulations. 

 2、 How we use cookies and similar technologies 
 n Cookies are text files placed on your access device by the web server, which will help you call information in subsequent visits and simplify the process of recording your personal information. 

 We send cookies to you to simplify the steps of repeated login, help judge your login status and the security of your account or data. We will not use Cookies for any purpose other than those stated in this privacy policy. 

 You have the right to accept or reject cookies. If the browser automatically receives cookies, you can modify the settings of the browser according to your needs to reject cookies. Please note that if you choose to reject cookies, you may not be able to fully experience the services provided by Fere fit. 

 3、 How do we share, transfer and publicly disclose your personal informatio
 
 n （1） Share 
 n We will not share your personal information with companies, organizations and individuals other than the service providers of the Feredit website, except for the following situations: 
 n (1) Obtain your explicit consent or authorization in advance; 

 (2) It shall be provided as necessary according to applicable laws and regulations, requirements of legal procedures, mandatory administrative or judicial requirements; 

 (3) To the extent permitted by laws and regulations, it is necessary to protect the interests, property or safety of Fere fit, its affiliates or partners, you or other users of Fere fit or the public from damage; 

 (4) Only by sharing your information can we realize the core functions of our goods and/or services or provide the services you need; 

 (5) Deal with disputes or controversies between you and others according to your needs; 

 (6) It is provided in accordance with relevant agreements signed with you (including electronic agreements signed online and corresponding platform rules) or other legal documents; 

 (7) Use based on academic research; 

 (8) It is used in accordance with the social public interest of laws and regulations. 

 We will share your personal information with our related parties. However, we will only share necessary personal information and are bound by the purpose stated in this privacy policy. If our related parties want to change the purpose of processing personal information, they will ask for your authorization again. 

 We will exchange information with other companies and organizations, but only to the extent permitted by laws and regulations, in order to optimize the service of Fere fit and protect the interests or security of Fere fit, you or other Fere fit customers. 

 We will share your order information, account information, equipment information and location information with partners and other third parties to ensure the smooth completion of the services provided to you. However, we will only share your personal information for legal, legitimate, necessary, specific and clear purposes, and only share the personal informatio
 necessary for providing services. Our partners have no right to use the shared personal information for any other purpose. Our partners include the following types: 
 n (1) A supplier of goods or technical services. We will share your personal information with the third party that supports our functions. These supports include providing us with goods or infrastructure technical services, logistics and distribution services, payment services, data processing, data analysis, etc. The purpose of sharing this information is to realize the core shopping function of our goods and/or services. For example, we must share your order information with the logistics service provider to arrange delivery; Or we need to share your order number and order amount with a third-party payment agency to confirm your payment instructions and complete payment. 

 (2) Third party merchants. We must share your order information and the necessary information related to the transaction with the third-party merchants to realize your demand for purchasing goods or services from them, and enable them to complete the subsequent after-sales service. 

 (3) Partners who entrust us with promotion. We will process relevant information, and the entrusting party will not directly identify you. 

 For companies, organizations and individuals with whom we share personal information, we will sign strict confidentiality agreements with them, requiring them to handle personal information in accordance with our instructions, this privacy policy and any other relevant confidentiality and security measures. 

 （2） Transfer 
 n We will not transfer your personal information to any company, organization or individual, except for the following circumstances: 
 n 1. Obtain your explicit consent or authorization in advance; 

 2. Provide according to applicable laws and regulations, requirements of legal procedures, mandatory administrative or judicial requirements; 

 3. It is provided in accordance with relevant agreements signed with you (including electronic agreements signed online and corresponding platform rules) or other legal documents; 

 4. When a merger, acquisition, asset transfer or similar transaction is involved, if personal information transfer is involved, we will require the new company or organization that holds your personal information to continue to be bound by this privacy policy, otherwise, we will require the company or organization to ask you for authorization consent again. 

 （3） Public disclosure 
 n We will only publicly disclose your personal information under the following circumstances: 
 n 1. According to your needs, disclose your designated personal information in the way you explicitly agree to disclose; 

 2. If your personal information must be provided according to the requirements of laws and regulations, mandatory administrative law enforcement or judicial requirements, we may publicly disclose your personal information according to the required type and disclosure method of personal information. On the premise of compliance with laws and regulations, when we receive the above request for information disclosure, we will require to issue the corresponding legal documents, such as subpoena or letter of investigation. 

 4、 How do we protect your personal informatio
 
 n （1） We have taken reasonable and feasible security measures in line with industry standards to protect the personal information provided by you from unauthorized access, public disclosure, use, modification, damage or loss. 

 （2） We have also taken strict management over the employees who may have access to your information to monitor their operations. We have established an approval mechanism for important operations such as data access, internal and external transmission, desensitization, and decryption, and signed confidentiality agreements with the above employees. At the same time, we also conduct regular information security training for employees, requiring them to form good operating habits in their daily work and improve their awareness of data protection. 

 （3） We will take reasonable and feasible measures to avoid collecting irrelevant personal information. We will only retain your personal information for the period required to achieve the purposes described in this policy, unless the retention period needs to be extended or permitted by law. 

 （4） The Internet is not an absolutely safe environment. Despite the aforementioned security measures, please understand that there are no perfect security measures on the network. We will provide appropriate security measures to protect your information according to the existing technology and provide reasonable security guarantees. We will try our best to prevent your information from being disclosed, damaged or lost. At the same time, please use a complex password and keep your account and password information properly. Don't tell others your password. If you find your personal information is leaked, especially your account and password, please contact us immediately so that we can take appropriate measures. 

 （5） In case of an unfortunate personal information security incident, we will inform you of the basic situation and possible impact of the security incident, the disposal measures we have taken or will take, the suggestions you can independently prevent and reduce risks, and the remedial measures for you in accordance with the requirements of laws and regulations. We will inform you of the event by mail, letter, telephone, push notification, etc. If it is difficult to inform the personal information subject one by one, we will take a reasonable and effective way to publish the announcement. At the same time, we will also report the disposition of personal information security incidents according to the requirements of the regulatory authorities. 

 5、 How do you manage your personal informatio
 
 n You can log in to Fere fit at any time to query, correct and delete your account information, modify your personal data, privacy settings, security settings, modify the shipping address and other personal information you provide when using the Fere fit service. If you have any questions, you can contact the Fere fit customer service. 

 You can log off the account on the website of Fere fit through the following path: call the customer service phone number published on the official website of Fere fit (such as 0755-29610919 in China), transfer to the customer service manual service according to the voice prompt, and complete the account cancellation after the customer verifies. After you cancel the account on the website of Fere fit, all the information in your account will be cleared, and we will no longer collect, use or share personal information related to the account. However, we still need to keep the previous information according to the regulatory requirements, and the competent authorities still have the right to inquire according to the law during the legally saved time. 

 To ensure security, you need to provide a written request or prove your identity in other ways. We will ask you to verify your identity before processing your request. We will reply within 30 days. If you are not satisfied, you can also make a complaint through the Fere fit customer service. 

 We will not be able to respond to your request as required by laws and regulations in the following cases: 
 n 1. Related to national security and national defense security; 

 2. Related to public safety, public health and major public interests; 

 3. Those related to criminal investigation, prosecution, trial and execution of judgments; 

 4. There is sufficient evidence to show that the subject of personal information has subjective malice or abuse of rights; 

 5. Responding to your request will cause serious damage to the legitimate rights and interests of you or other individuals and organizations; 

 6. Involving trade secrets. 

 6、 How do we handle minors personal informatio
 
 n We attach great importance to the protection of minors' personal information. If you are a minor under the age of 18, you should obtain the written consent of your parent or legal guardian before using the service of the website. 

 In the case of collecting personal information of minors by using our goods or services with the consent of parents or guardians, we will only use, share, transfer or disclose this information when laws and regulations permit, parents or guardians expressly agree or it is necessary to protect minors. 

 If we find that we have collected personal information of minors without the prior consent of verifiable parents or legal guardians, we will try to delete relevant data as soon as possible. 

 7、 How does this privacy policy update 
 n We will change our privacy policy when necessary. Without your explicit consent, we will not reduce your rights under this privacy policy. 

 For major changes, we will also provide more significant notifications (including notification and even pop-up prompts to you through the way of publicity on the Fere fit website). Please visit this privacy policy frequently to read the latest version. 

 Major changes referred to in this policy include but are not limited to: n n 1. Our service model has undergone significant changes. For example, the purpose of processing personal information, the type of personal information processed, and the use mode of personal information; 

 2. Significant changes have taken place in our control rights and other aspects. For example, changes in owners caused by mergers and acquisitions; 

 3. The main objects of personal information sharing, transfer or public disclosure have changed; 

 4. Your right to participate in personal information processing and the way you exercise it have changed significantly; 

 5. When the responsible department, contact information and complaint channel for handling personal information security change; 

 6. When the personal information security impact assessment report indicates that there is a high risk. 

 We will also archive the old version of this policy for your reference. 

 8、 How to contact us 

 You can contact us in the following ways, and we will reply to your request within 30 days: 

 1. If you have any questions, comments or suggestions on the content of this policy, you can send an email to 936160908@qq.com Or call our customer service number and other ways to contact us; 

 2. We have also set up a special department for personal information protection (or personal information protection specialist). You can send an email to 936160908@qq.com To contact them. 

 If you are not satisfied with our reply, especially if our personal information processing has damaged your legitimate rights and interests, you can also complain or report to the regulatory authorities such as Netcom, Telecom, Public Security and Industry and Commerce.

"heart_rate_description" : "Heart rate refers to the number of heart beats per minute in a normal person's quiet state, also known as the quiet heart rate, which is generally 60-100 beats per minute. Individual differences may occur due to age, gender or other physiological factors. PPG photoelectric heart rate measurement method is to use the green light emitted by the optical sensor to irradiate the blood vessel to obtain the absorbance change of blood hemoglobin in the blood vessel to measure the pulse. The sensor is equipped with an infrared emitting beam circuit and a receiving reflection circuit. Because the signal is extremely weak, it is not easy to be interfered by the outside world, resulting in inaccurate measurement data, And generally need to be measured in a quiet state, not suitable for continuous measurement of heart rate during exercise. When wearing the wrist, please keep the wrist free of water, sweat and shaking, and press the sensor on the back of the device tightly to the skin and blood vessels of the wrist as far as possible."

"help" : "1. Connect the device Open the Bluetooth function of the mobile phone, click app settings - my device - add device, and the mobile phone will automatically search for the device device. When the device is in the normal startup state, the device name will appear. Click the device name to connect. 2. Can't find the device? When the device is close to the mobile phone and can't find the device, please check whether the device is turned on or the power is exhausted. If the device name appears after searching for the device, but you can't connect by clicking, please try to turn off the Bluetooth function of the mobile phone and turn it on again, or turn it on again. If you have other devices connected to your mobile phone before, be sure to delete or disconnect them, and then search and connect the device device again. Apple mobile phone users need to go to mobile phone system Settings > Bluetooth > click on the right side of the connected device while app unbinds the device Symbol > ignore this device, otherwise app will not be able to find this device in the next search. 3. Description of step counting data and sleep monitoring data When you find that the step data is not synchronized with the device, or the app step data is not updated, please try to manually synchronize the data. Sometimes the data stored in the device is too large, and it takes a certain amount of time for Bluetooth to automatically update the data. In addition, we collect real-time step data through motion sensors, compare the weight and height of men and women and other personal setting information, convert and analyze the closest to the real step environment, so as to distinguish different movements such as fast running, jogging and walking. When the device starts Bluetooth connection, the movement steps of the device are not included at the beginning of the action. Only when you actually walk dozens of times, the device will start to recognize the movement state and start to include the steps. Therefore, you will find that when the device starts Bluetooth connection, the device may ignore the steps. In addition, sleep monitoring is analyzed and calculated by grabbing the built-in motion sensor data of the device, so to test the sleep data, you must wear the device before you go to sleep. Except for some devices, you can manually set the sleeping time, but most of the device devices automatically enter the sleep monitoring mode at night, and can't detect the sleep data during the day. 4. Installation of APP / APK requirements for mobile phone system The mobile phone must be Android 4.3 and IOS 7.0 or above to install software and connect the device device“"

"blood_glucose_introduction" : "Blood glucose generally refers to the glucose content in the blood. The commonly used clinical blood glucose value is the serum glucose value, which refers to the blood glucose value measured by venous blood. Generally, fasting blood glucose is 3.9-6.1 mmol/L, and the normal value of postprandial blood glucose is also different according to the time: blood glucose at 1 hour after meal should be less than 11.1 mmol/L, and blood glucose at 2 hours after meal should be 3.9-7.8 mmol/L. The test value is for reference only and cannot be used as medical diagnosis"

high.description:

hotspot.title: Found 22 critical permission(s)
hotspot.description:
Ensure that these permissions are required by the application.

android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE (dangerous): read/modify/delete external storage contents - Allows an application to write to external storage.

android.permission.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE (dangerous): read external storage contents - Allows an application to read from external storage.

android.permission.READ_MEDIA_IMAGES (dangerous): allows reading image files from external storage. - Allows an application to read image files from external storage.

android.permission.BLUETOOTH_SCAN (dangerous): required for discovering and pairing Bluetooth devices. - Required to be able to discover and pair nearby Bluetooth devices.

android.permission.BLUETOOTH_CONNECT (dangerous): necessary for connecting to paired Bluetooth devices. - Required to be able to connect to paired Bluetooth devices.

android.permission.BLUETOOTH_ADVERTISE (dangerous): required to advertise to nearby Bluetooth devices. - Required to be able to advertise to nearby Bluetooth devices.

android.permission.POST_NOTIFICATIONS (dangerous): allows an app to post notifications. - Allows an app to post notifications

android.permission.ANSWER_PHONE_CALLS (dangerous): permits an app to answer incoming phone calls. - Allows the app to answer an incoming phone call.

android.permission.CALL_PHONE (dangerous): directly call phone numbers - Allows the application to call phone numbers without your intervention. Malicious applications may cause unexpected calls on your phone bill. Note that this does not allow the application to call emergency numbers.

android.permission.READ_LOGS (dangerous): read sensitive log data - Allows an application to read from the system's various log files. This allows it to discover general information about what you are doing with the phone, potentially including personal or private information.

android.permission.ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATION (dangerous): coarse (network-based) location - Access coarse location sources, such as the mobile network database, to determine an approximate phone location, where available. Malicious applications can use this to determine approximately where you are.

android.permission.ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION (dangerous): fine (GPS) location - Access fine location sources, such as the Global Positioning System on the phone, where available. Malicious applications can use this to determine where you are and may consume additional battery power.

android.permission.READ_PHONE_STATE (dangerous): read phone state and identity - Allows the application to access the phone features of the device. An application with this permission can determine the phone number and serial number of this phone, whether a call is active, the number that call is connected to and so on.

android.permission.READ_CALL_LOG (dangerous): grants read access to the user's call log. - Allows an application to read the user's call log.

android.permission.RECEIVE_SMS (dangerous): receive SMS - Allows application to receive and process SMS messages. Malicious applications may monitor your messages or delete them without showing them to you.

android.permission.READ_CONTACTS (dangerous): read contact data - Allows an application to read all of the contact (address) data stored on your phone. Malicious applications can use this to send your data to other people.

android.permission.ACCESS_BACKGROUND_LOCATION (dangerous): access location in background - Allows an app to access location in the background.

android.permission.WRITE_SETTINGS (dangerous): modify global system settings - Allows an application to modify the system's settings data. Malicious applications can corrupt your system's configuration.

android.permission.CAMERA (dangerous): take pictures and videos - Allows application to take pictures and videos with the camera. This allows the application to collect images that the camera is seeing at any time.

android.permission.RECORD_AUDIO (dangerous): record audio - Allows application to access the audio record path.

android.permission.SYSTEM_ALERT_WINDOW (dangerous): display system-level alerts - Allows an application to show system-alert windows. Malicious applications can take over the entire screen of the phone.

android.permission.GET_TASKS (dangerous): retrieve running applications - Allows application to retrieve information about currently and recently running tasks. May allow malicious applications to discover private information about other applications.
